headshotImage.caption: Devendra Bishoo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Devendra Bishoo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Bishoo takes out Shehzad! Another lovely leg break, luring Shehzad forward by the flight, before it dipped and turned away from him. Shehzad wasn't looking for the big hit; he didn't throw his wicket; he was just done in by a good delivery. He leaned forward to just defend but dragged his back foot outside the crease and was done in by the flight, loop, and turn. Stumped!

Bishoo strikes again. Hafeez has done it again. Hmm.. Credit to Bishoo for slowing down the pace  but Hafeez could have done much better with it than pushing it tamely to short midwicket. He was looking to clip it to the on side but was done in by the slower pace and shoveled it straight, and softly, to midwicket

headshotImage.longCaption: Devendra Bishoo player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Shafiq decides to turn into umar Akmal for fun and has a big heave to the leg side and edges it to third man. Pakistan complete a comprehensive victory here.

commentPostTextItems.html: The spinners strangled West Indies, who limped to 221 before Pakistan batted serenely to achieve the target without any fuss.
Hang on for the quotes from the post-match ceremony

Sammy: "We dug ourselves into a hole when the spinners were bowling. we have to come better in the next game. i was surprised to see the spin and bounce in this wicket; we have to work in nets and come back on monday. We need to show more intent. We need more work in the nets with Dessie (desmond haynes). We will look to improve. We didnt get line and length, too many boundary balls .."

Afridi: "When Sammy said he wanted to bat, I was very happy. The boys did a great job. I did expect the pitch to turn; there was moisture on it and I know my boys are capable of doing it. Wahab is very talented; He did well agianst India ... he should be more focussed on his bowling;. Misbah proved that he is still alive and doing a great job!"

Man of the match is Hafeez: "I am doing hard work in the nets with the coaches. I am grateful to the coaches. The role given to me .. the captain is using me well. i try to restrict the batsman and I am getting the wickets with that. I just want to continue this form and contribute to the team. I am very happy that the team is doing well."

commentTextItems.html: on the middle and leg, angling in, flicked away to the deep to collect two more and tie up the score.
leans forward to play this to the leg side for a single

commentPreTextItems.html: Sabeen: "@Ahad I kinda think Pakistan need a combination of Akmal's and Shafiq's styles. Akmal is perfect for the last few overs and the batting powerplay. He adds excitement to the line up specially when Afridi isn't performing with the bat."

commentTextItems.html: short in length, cut down to third man

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad st †Baugh b Bishoo 22 (39b 4x4 0x6 48m) SR: 56.41

dismissalComment.html: Bishoo takes out Shehzad! Another lovely leg break, luring Shehzad forward by the flight, before it dipped and turned away from him. Shehzad wasn't looking for the big hit; he didn't throw his wicket; he was just done in by a good delivery. He leaned forward to just defend but dragged his back foot outside the crease and was done in by the flight, loop, and turn. Stumped!

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Sammy b Bishoo 54 (45b 7x4 1x6 67m) SR: 120

dismissalComment.html: Bishoo strikes again. Hafeez has done it again. Hmm.. Credit to Bishoo for slowing down the pace  but Hafeez could have done much better with it than pushing it tamely to short midwicket. He was looking to clip it to the on side but was done in by the slower pace and shoveled it straight, and softly, to midwicket
